BRIEFING:
DRY AND STABLE CONDITIONS WILL PERSIST TODAY, WITH LIGHT WINDS AND WIDESPREAD VFR CONDITIONS. TRADE WINDS WILL GRADUALLY STRENGTHEN TONIGHT AND SATURDAY, LIKELY BRINGING AN INCREASE IN WINDWARD SHOWERS OVER MAUI AND THE BIG ISLAND, LEADING TO AREAS OF MVFR VIS/CIG IN SHRA, AND BRIGNING THE POTENTIAL FOR MOUNTAIN OBSCURATION.
THREAT: NO SIGMETS IN AREA OF OPERATION.
